<h1>Problem 1404 - 2015 EGMO, P2 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>A <i>domino</i> is a \(2 \times 1\) or \(1 \times 2\) tile. Determine in how many ways exactly \(n^2\) dominoes can be placed without overlapping on a \(2n \times 2n\) chessboard so that every \(2 \times 2\) square contains at least two uncovered unit squares which lie in the same row or column.</p>
